@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "HipBarr" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that HipBarr runs
      fine on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with
      a 68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To play, just click on a tile that contains part of a bar, this
will make the bar rotate clockwise by 90 degrees around the tile
you clicked on... of course, the next tile where the bar will go
must be empty. Also, the bar cannot cross another bar that is
placed nearby. As there are other bars that may interfere with the
movement of a bar, these must also be moved when needed.

  The idea is to move the coloured bar so part of it is placed on
the exit tile, which is indicated by a 'pressed down' rectangle, at
the lower right position on the game board. Complete each board in
the least amount of moves...

  If you get stuck on a game board, click on the 'Replay' button to
restart the current game board. However, note that the number of
moves you make on a game board accumulates until you complete
it...

  Have fun!

OPTIONS
-------

  Replay: To restart the current game board.

  Colour: To change the colour of the coloured bar.

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

